Function merge_batch_results 

Source 
pub(crate) fn merge_batch_results(
    cached: Vec<Option<Embedding>>,
    results: Vec<Embedding>,
) -> Vec<Embedding>
Expand description

Merge cached hits with provider results for a batch operation.

Given the original cached lookup (Some = hit, None = miss) and the provider results for just the misses, reassembles the full output in original order.

§Panics

Panics if results.len() doesn’t match the number of None entries in cached (i.e. the provider didn’t return the expected count).
